						               													<description>Solar Century is a heavy strategy game with combinative card play that aims to capture the political theatre of interplanetary colonization on a grand scale.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players act as the Council of the Imperator who rules the solar system. Each turn marks the passing of ten unified solar years.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting the game, the Council drafts four colonies who send their leaders to explore and conquer planets. Players wield influence over these colony leaders to initiate actions and they have a century to prove themself to the Imperator or take over its Seat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round has three phases:&amp;#10;- AUDIENCE: ask the Imperator to send agents to a region of the solar system,&amp;#10;- COLONIZATION: either make alliances or wield influence on an ally to initiate and action up to two times,&amp;#10;- SOLSTICE: develop a colony and prepare for the next turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player within the Council wins with&amp;#10;- the most influence over the colony, which controls at least six planets at the end of a round (absolute win) or&amp;#10;- the most victory points at the end of the century (capital win).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
